quotedTweet.rawContent:
Depression isn’t “crying and dressing in black.” 

For many, it’s not even sadness at all—it’s nothing, literally, a numbness so strong, feeling doesn’t exist, and all that’s left is a shell of self.

Integrated treatment can help many to feel alive again. 

It CAN get better.

I pass through hands
Like grains of sand
Tiny pieces of rainbow glass
Broken, but beautiful
Stepped on, but felt
I am the earth
I am everywhere
But nowhere 
All the same

Sadness is an emotion.

When someone suffering from depression says: “I’m fine”

What they may mean is:
I was just crying.
I feel alone.
I feel empty.
I wish the pain would end.
I’m numb.
I’m scared.

PAY ATTENTION to subtle cues.
GIVE A FK.❤️
#love #grief #depression
